Revision history for openvpn

0.04 2026-05-01
    - expanded `cpanfile` so it explicitly records the core Perl modules used by the skill and names the skill-local modules separately

0.03 2026-05-01
    - added an explicit `cpanfile` to keep the dependency gate present even though the skill currently uses only Perl core modules and skill-local modules

0.02 2026-05-01
    - created the initial `openvpn` skill with setup, connect, disconnect, and noreconnect commands
    - added collector-backed OpenVPN connection monitoring with auto reconnect and retry exhaustion handling
    - stored OpenVPN credentials in `~/.openvpn.env` and generated auth-user-pass files from that state
    - added TOTP and `otpauth://` secret handling for six-digit reconnect suffix generation
    - removed package-manager installation of `openvpn` and moved process control into skill-owned Perl modules
    - added Windows 11 PowerShell-aware launcher behavior for `openvpn.exe`, pid checks, and config discovery
